The paper deals with the generation of random traces of concurrent systems, which is a topic in the intersection of several subfields of computer science. However, the focus on Bernoulli sequences and the use of probabilistic measures suggests that the paper is most likely to be classified under Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Information Theory (cs.IT). The study of synchronization of sequences also suggests a connection to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). Finally, the mention of distributed and incremental generation of executions suggests a connection to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
